-- Retired: the English prompt router.
--   parse_ask(prompt) -> (ask_kind, phrase, phrase2, type_name)   [pg_laplace_parse_ask]
-- The ~30-pattern English regex ladder that guessed a read intent and a relation
-- type from the surface form of a prompt is gone; recall_intent() takes the shape
-- and the resolved ids as arguments instead. The C symbol pg_laplace_parse_ask no
-- longer exists in the .so, so on the UPGRADE path (which only CREATE-OR-REPLACEs
-- the manifest files and never drops what left it) the old catalog row would
-- linger bound to a missing symbol — an orphan that errors on every call. A fresh
-- CREATE EXTENSION never had it; this DROP makes the upgraded catalog match.
DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS parse_ask(text);
